# Hardened Docker DooD Sandbox Service

## Overview
This provider creates a hardened, sterile execution environment for the Sandbox
service. If your OpenClaw agent hallucinates a dangerous Python or Bash script,
or is tricked via prompt injection into running malicious code, this environment
ensures the code cannot escape and compromise your host machine. By utilizing
Docker-out-of-Docker (DooD) principles, the main gateway routes all code
execution requests into this isolated container rather than executing them
internally.

### Security Posture
* **Network Isolation:** The sandbox has no access to the internet or your
  internal `openclaw-net` Docker network. It cannot exfiltrate data or scan
  internal ports.
* **Capability Dropping:** All Linux kernel capabilities are explicitly dropped
  (`cap_drop: ALL`).
* **No New Privileges:** The container is forbidden from gaining new privileges
  via setuid binaries.

<h2 id="env.vars">Pre-Flight Environment Configuration</h2>

This service runs entirely locally and requires no external API keys. You may
safely proceed with the default configuration.
